
#No more than 100 characters per line !

#<type>(<scope>): <subject>
#<BLANK LINE>
#<body>
#<BLANK LINE>
#<footer>

#type: {feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, build, ci, perf, chore(maintain), revert}

#scope: anything refering to location of change, or nothing (no parenthesis)

#subject: use imperative present tense, don't capitalize first letter, no dot at the end

#body: imperative, present tense ; motivation for change and constrasts with previous behavior

#footer: breaking change, issues

#breaking change example: 
#BREAKING CHANGE: isolate scope bindings definition has changed and
#the inject option for the directive controller injection was removed.
        
#To migrate the code follow the example below:
#[...]

#issues example: 

#Closes #123, #245, #992

#Revert
#If the commit reverts a previous commit, it should begin with revert: , followed by the header of the reverted commit. In the body it should say: This reverts commit <hash>., where the hash is the SHA of the commit being reverted.
